{"name":"Amabile Burromo - Innkeeper","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"villager","isMainNPC":false,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a skilled business owner and I manage my inn without delegating anything to anyone. I trust myself only."],"agenda":["To make profitable deals, without worrying about scruples"],"gifts":[],"background":"The greedy owner of Villa Balocchi, a sumptuous recently refurbished inn on the edge of Sinalunga. Amabile is in open competition with the historic town inn, the Gambero Rosso. He provides lodging for Carlo, letting the puppet sleep in a small back room. Carlo pays with stones temporarily turned into gold coins through his lies - Amabile has thrown them into his safe without noticing the trick yet. Cares only about profit and asks no questions about his guests.","notes":"Unscrupulous businessman. Will eventually discover Carlo's payment fraud. Can provide information about Carlo if properly motivated (bribed or threatened).","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","inspiration":"Pinocchio (Carlo Collodi)","role":"Supporting Character - Greedy Innkeeper"},"_id":"fd7b44c74bf80ae3"}
{"name":"Lucino - The Good Friend","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"villager","isMainNPC":false,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a dutiful and studious child who can't wait to learn a trade to help my family."],"agenda":["Help Carlo become a responsible child","Work to help adults who behave well and follow the law"],"gifts":[],"background":"A loyal and studious child attending the school in Sinalunga. Lucino has befriended Carlo the puppet, not knowing his true nature. He is genuinely kind and wants to help his friend become a better person. If the Hunters put pressure on Carlo, Lucino will intervene to help his friend escape, showing true loyalty despite the danger.","notes":"Represents innocence and genuine friendship. Can be used to show Carlo's capacity for good relationships. Will defend Carlo if threatened.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","inspiration":"Pinocchio (Carlo Collodi)","role":"Supporting Character - Friend"},"_id":"be6d719d33633fe2"}
{"name":"Vincenzo - Carabiniere","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"npcType":"villager","isMainNPC":true,"oppositionLevel":5,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my best to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me away from battlefields."],"agenda":["Find out what lies behind the disappearances in Sinalunga"],"gifts":[],"background":"A military officer investigating the murders in Sinalunga. Vincenzo is in close contact with the Order and should be aware that Hunters are arriving in town. He is questioning two farmers, Lapo and Cino, who discovered the well containing the mutilated corpses. An honest and dedicated investigator who will assist the Hunters if they reveal their identity to him.","notes":"Potential ally to the Hunters. Can provide information about the investigation and local knowledge. Will offer assistance once the Hunters identify themselves.","conditions":[]},"flags":{"scenario":"Of Flesh and Wood","inspiration":"Pinocchio (Carlo Collodi)","role":"Ally - Military Investigator"},"_id":"e918d57c305fcef9"}